<br>
Its very possible to hand out muffins to folks and then pop someone in the jaw for training you without warning. hehe Some characters who have cute elements also have a depth beyond that...<br>
<br>
Teirra comes to mind when I think of cute, kind, and unusual Tier'dal. If there were a hundred Teirra's running around it might get a bit much, however. *smiles and hugs the nearest skelly*<br>
<br>
In regard to Kimaya's situation, and NPCs relating information versus PCs doing so, I should think most folks would believe the one they know better, as is usually the case IRL.<br>
<br>
Friend A, who you know and trust, tells you something. Then Random Entity A tells you something different. Who do you believe? IRL, most people would believe their friend I should think, so if Kimaya has a believable explination for the pixie situation my characters would be inclined to accept it if it was plausible and they trusted her.<br>
<br>
Of course, if Random Entity A is in a position of authority or specializes in the subject, that may or may not change things for some people. Is the ranger in a position to have knowledge that Kimaya doesnt? Does he have a vested interest in the whole thing? Perhaps the Defenders of Kelethin are overzealous about protecting their Tree City from fires?<br>
<br>
The reason I found this particularly interesting it that it does have a very real bearing on the current situation in the US. Do people accept what the government states is the truth, without looking deeper? What about the media? Do you accept what most people say is true, or do you believe half of what you see and none of what you hear?<br>
<br>
I myself have learned to be a skeptic in the face of many, many deceptions...<br>
<br>
Buran McMuffin, the original Iron Chef<br>
**Slayin gnolls n makin muffins from 3174-3177**<br>
*Now only makin muffins*<br>
<br>
Domenic Dominion<br>
